<div class="recipe">
<p>Everyone has probably had roasted potatoes, but we gaurantee you haven't had any like this before. These potatoes will develop a beautiful, almost glass-like exterior while the inside remains incredibly fluffy.</p>
<p>What's the secret to the crispiness? Well, it comes from first boiling the potatoes in a basic solution. This will help break down the outer layer of starch around the potatoes. When baked, the loose starch is what will harden into a crisp shell. After boiling the potatoes, we will also have you vigourously shake the potatoes to roughen up their exterior. This will provide more surface area to expose more of that loosened starch to get even crispier.</p>
<p>To flavour these potatoes, we will use an oil infused with various herbs and garlic. It is important to strain the herbs and garlic from the oil or else you will risk those ingredients burning as it bakes. Alternatively, you can use less oil and season with simple salt and pepper at the end of cooking, up to you. However, it is essential to use some oil if you want the potatoes to be as crispy as possible.</p>
<p>It is very important to use a brown variety of potato, such as a Yukon Gold or Russett potato. A red-skinned potato contains more moisture and won't bake up as crispy.</p>
